throughout their hospitalization the dehydration status of each patient was closely monitored clinically, including the measurement of blood pressure and pulse rate. no laboratory tests were done systematically, but blood glucose level was measured in cases where hypoglycemia was suspected.during the early phases of haiti's cholera epidemic, we observed several cases of severe hypoglycemia in adults. as a preventive measure, all pregnant women in our cholera unit therefore received a 50 ml bolus of 50% glucose upon admission. patients who were vomiting or unable to drink ors received an additional 50 ml of 50% glucose in each liter of ringer's lactate. the level of plasma glucose was monitored and replacement adjusted accordingly.
